<section class="section">
  <h2>About the Book</h2>
  <p>
    <em>Cuba, Your Children Cry</em> is a cultural and historical memoir examining the
    Cuban refugee experience through personal narrative and historical context.
    Otto H. Iglesias explores exile, identity, and generational memory, offering a
    deeply human account of displacement and resilience.
  </p>
</section>

<section class="section alt">
  <h2>About the Author</h2>
  <p>
    Otto H. Iglesias is a first-generation Cuban American born and raised in Miami,
    Florida. The son of Cuban refugees, his work focuses on exile, cultural identity,
    and historical preservation.
  </p>
  <p>
    He earned a Juris Doctor from Michigan State University College of Law and an LL.M.
    in Trial Advocacy from Temple University. He currently resides in Rhode Island
    with his spouse and son.
  </p>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <h2>Awards & Recognition</h2>
